    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.6.5" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">5</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    Pearson's Magazine
                        <lb/>
                    Incorporated.
                        <lb/>
                    34 Union Square New York
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        29 Waverly Place,
                        New York.
                        Apr. 30, 1919.
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Thank you for offering to send me a review of Upton Sinclair's "The Profits of Religion," but I do not care for this book particularly and don't think I could use a review of it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours very truly,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Frank Harris
                
                    Editor,
                    PEARSON'S MAGAZINE.
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note place="bottom" type="recipient">Dear Sinclair:&#8212; 
                    Did I write you about this? It seems to me that I did, but I'm not sure. What is wrong with Harris?
                    Yours,
                    John Neihardt
                    
                    May 10, '19.</note> 
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
